To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Minnesota Government Data Practices Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am searching for the following report, performed by the Minnesota Department of Health in 1978: Evaluation of Employee Exposure to Asbestos at the MacArthur Company, St. Paul, MN. Minneapolis, MN.

In addition to this report, I am looking for all correspondence, memos, studies, evaluations, reports, plans of action, recommendations, and/or citations between the MacArthur Company in St. Paul, MN and the Minnesota Dept. of Health.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Kevin LaMarca

title: Santa Teresa High School Incident Report

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Santa Teresa High School Incident Report
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The incident report and any supplements, such as police narratives, and/or investigative reports produced in relation to the shooting incident at Santa Teresa High School on 9/9/1999 either a full, redacted, or partial release of these documents.

In the event that there are fees, I would request a waiver, as I am a member of a nonprofit media outlet and these records will be used in the public interest. 

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. 

I would prefer the request filed electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,
Daniella Jimenez
Investigative Reporting Workshop.

title: Open Records Request: Ohio Violent Crime Reduction Grant

communications.subject: Ohio Open Records Law Request: Open Records Request: Ohio Violent Crime Reduction Grant
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

According to a press release from Gov. Mike DeWine's office, the Youngstown Police Department received a grant of $1,862,761.84 as part of the Ohio Violent Crime Reduction Grant program: https://content.govdelivery.com/attachments/OHIOGOVERNOR/2023/02/22/file_attachments/2416264/Violent%20Crime%20Reduction%20Program%20Grant%20Summaries%20through%20R12.pdf

Pursuant to the Ohio Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of all documents, including but not limited to, applications, agreements, and reporting documents for the Youngstown Police Department's grant of $1,862,761.84 as part of the Ohio Violent Crime Reduction Grant program described in the press release linked above.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

e
